.TH LE-VIBE-SETUP-CONTINUE 1 "2026" "Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
le-vibe-setup-continue \- symlink Lé Vibe Continue config and install pinned Continue + YAML extensions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B le-vibe-setup-continue
.RB [ \-\-gui ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs
.BR sync\-continue\-config.sh
then
.BR install\-continue\-extension.sh
(which installs pinned
.B continue.continue
and
.B redhat.vscode\-yaml
from Open VSX per
.BR docs/continue\-extension\-pin.md )
with clear exit codes (see below). Run as the desktop user after
.B lvibe
has completed first\-run and written
.IR ~/.config/le\-vibe/continue\-config.yaml
(same launcher as
.BR le\-vibe (1)).

After successful first\-run, \fBlvibe\fR may invoke this command automatically; set \fBLE_VIBE_AUTO_CONTINUE_SETUP=0\fR to disable. See \fBlvibe\fR(1) / \fBle\-vibe\fR(1) DESCRIPTION.

With
.BR \-\-gui ,
if the Continue YAML exists, shows a Zenity dialog asking whether to run the
same steps now (requires the
.B zenity
package). Choosing \*(lqNot now\*(rq exits 0. If the YAML is missing, shows an
error dialog and exits 1.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
No Lé Vibe Continue YAML yet; run
.B lvibe
first (compatibility name:
.BR le\-vibe (1)).
.TP
.B 2
Config sync failed.
.TP
.B 3
Extension install failed (Continue or YAML; network or marketplace).
.TP
.B 4
No editor binary (install VSCodium or set
.BR LE_VIBE_EDITOR ).
.TP
.B 127
Helper scripts not found, or
.B \-\-gui
was used without
.B zenity
installed.
.TP
.B 125
Unknown CLI option (see
.BR \-\-help ).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lvibe (1),
.BR le\-vibe (1),
.BR codium (1).
.PP
Full post\-install steps and policy summary: \fI/usr/share/doc/le\-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
